---
Midgaard's administrative relationship with the Cinderteeth is primarily defined by the Ashfall Monsoon and its institutional aftermath: the eruption produced the displacement crisis Midgaard's resettlement apparatus processed under the Violet Compact, classifying Ashborn survivors as a human subtype — a classification the Continuity faction has maintained against persistent Reckoning-faction challenges.
Midgaard charter jurisdiction over the Chalkwind Saddle route houses is contested but functional; the Blackstep Footholds boundary dispute remains unresolved, currently operating under a joint warden commission.
The sealed warrants covering Ashfall displacement records are stored under the same warrant system the Continuity faction uses to deny Ashborn reclassification petitions.
Midgaard's Granite Arcade archives hold Conclave-era correspondence including references to the Western Fold sanctum and condemned-labor transfers routed along Roc Road toward "the mountain academy."
Obsidian and sulfur trade from the Glasswash Fans feeds Midgaard's alchemical processing networks.
Seismic monitoring of the Bellspine crystals is nominally the responsibility of the Wizard's Keep containment office, which has not funded a survey expedition in eleven years.
Ash Cult activity in the Ember Crown is classified as frontier religious variance rather than organized threat.

