The Conclave's interference in the Western Fold was a category error: treating the mountain as a problem to be instrumented rather than a system to be read. The resonance crystals, tuned to Conclave operational frequencies rather than mountain frequencies, are still trying to impose calibration on processes that predate them by geological ages.
Kethari in Midgaard hold no formal role in Cinderteeth governance but are occasionally consulted informally by warden commissions in the Blackstep Footholds.
The Ashfall Monsoon's timing, in Kethari geological memory, was predictable from long-cycle pattern indicators that no human institution had been tracking.

